  "text": "The finite time blow-up problem for the incompressible Navier-Stokes equations has been viewed in light of complex singularities [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The robustness with which complex singularities are located and visualized in Figure 3 .2 suggests that computing the distance of the singularities from the real t-axis as a function of the Reynolds number may shed some light on this topic. However, there is a subtle difference between mathematical and computational investigations of finite time blow-up.",
